    <h2>Respect for Copyright</h2>
    <p>HelloDeploy users must have the rights necessary to deploy their repositories and hosted content. Copyright infringement is prohibited by the <a href="/acceptable-use">Acceptable Use Policy</a>.</p>

    <h2>Reporting Copyright Infringement</h2>
    <p>To report allegedly infringing content hosted through HelloDeploy, email <strong>hensonsagorsor@gmail.com</strong> with:</p>
    <ul>
      <li>Your name and contact information.</li>
      <li>A description of the copyrighted work you claim is infringed.</li>
      <li>The URL or project hostname where the allegedly infringing material appears.</li>
      <li>A statement that you have a good-faith belief that the use is not authorized by the copyright owner, agent, or law.</li>
      <li>A statement that the information in your notice is accurate and that you are the copyright owner or authorized to act for the owner.</li>
      <li>Your physical or electronic signature.</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>Counter-Notice</h2>
    <p>If your content was removed or disabled because of a copyright complaint and you believe the action was mistaken, email a counter-notice with your contact information, the removed material, the reason you believe removal was mistaken, and your physical or electronic signature.</p>

    <h2>Repeat Infringers</h2>
    <p>HelloDeploy may suspend or terminate accounts or projects that repeatedly infringe copyright or repeatedly receive valid copyright complaints.</p>

    <h2>Important Notice</h2>
    <p>This policy is a practical pilot process and is not a substitute for formal legal advice. If HelloDeploy is operated as a public service in the United States, the operator should consider registering a DMCA designated agent with the U.S. Copyright Office.</p>
  </div>
